Nuclear – Capula




















































 
















AboutHistorySenior Management TeamVertical MarketsNuclearDefenceFuel Production & ReprocessingNew BuildResearch & DevelopmentDecommissioningWaste Management & StoragePower GenerationRenewablesPower TransmissionWaterOil and GasProcess IndustriesCapabilitiesSystems     Substation Automation – IMPERIUM     Material Tracking     Boiler Control     DCS     Telemetry     SCADA     PLC     Safety SystemsService     Support ContractsAsset Management24/7 SupportLong Term Support ContractsObsolescence Management     System Upgrades     Technical Audits     Cyber Security     Panel Build     Security Management     Repairs Service     Consultancy     Health Checks     Migration     TrainingSoftware Solutions     OPUS Building Management Performance     Transmission Networks – IMPERIUM     Situational Awareness     Network VisibilityCase StudiesPartnersMediaWorking At CapulaOur PeopleProfilesDeveloping TalentGraduate ProgrammeVacanciesContactSearch









 











Loading...



















NuclearWith over 40 years’ experience in the nuclear industry, Capula supports the full life cycle of nuclear energy from new build to waste management and decommissioning.
In decommissioning and waste management, our systems safely control the processing and storage, while in operations our solutions are used for new fuel production and also enable nuclear generation to continue as a viable option in the UK’s energy strategy.
We apply our nuclear and automation expertise to the defence sector through a wide range of mission critical programmes.  Our systems and solutions help our clients optimise their research, design, manufacturing and maintenance operations whilst enabling regulatory compliance with environmental and safety standards.




Nuclear
Defence
Fuel Production & Reprocessing
Nuclear Power Generation
New Build
Research & Development
