Working At Capula – Capula




















































 
















AboutHistorySenior Management TeamVertical MarketsNuclearDefenceFuel Production & ReprocessingNew BuildResearch & DevelopmentDecommissioningWaste Management & StoragePower GenerationRenewablesPower TransmissionWaterOil and GasProcess IndustriesCapabilitiesSystems     Substation Automation – IMPERIUM     Material Tracking     Boiler Control     DCS     Telemetry     SCADA     PLC     Safety SystemsService     Support ContractsAsset Management24/7 SupportLong Term Support ContractsObsolescence Management     System Upgrades     Technical Audits     Cyber Security     Panel Build     Security Management     Repairs Service     Consultancy     Health Checks     Migration     TrainingSoftware Solutions     OPUS Building Management Performance     Transmission Networks – IMPERIUM     Situational Awareness     Network VisibilityCase StudiesPartnersMediaWorking At CapulaOur PeopleProfilesDeveloping TalentGraduate ProgrammeVacanciesContactSearch









 















 Working at CapulaCapula recognises the importance our people play in achieving continued success for the company and encourages the development of long-term relationships with our clients and suppliers.
We believe it is the quality of our people that sets Capula apart from our competitors, and this is underpinned by our approach to staff development to continue to meet our business objectives and encourage of individuals who demonstrate initiative and take responsibility for results.
Capula nurtures a positive working environment through team building exercises, and social activities co-ordinated via the in-house Capula Employee Association.
To express an interest in any positions at Capula, please e-mail recruitment@capula.co.uk with a cover letter and CV attached.





